div1.p: United States District Court Western District of Washington Northern Division
In the Matter of the Application of Ching Hing for a Writ of Habeas Corpus } No. 28752857 Order.

Upon the motion of Albert Moodie, Assistant United States Attorney, for the Western District of Washington, it appearing that there has been deposited in the Registry of this Court the sum of One Hundred Dollars, to cover expense of maintence of the petitioner in the above entitled cause, same having been deposited by John J. Sullivan, Esq., attorney for petitioner; and it further appearing from the affidavit of Henry M. White, Commissioner of Immigration, hereto attached, that the attached bill in favor of J. Richard Lane in the sumn of Ninety-three and 40/100 Dollars ($93.40) is a just bill, and the court being advised that J. Richard Lane mentioned in the affidavit is the same party who furnished meals to the petitioner in the above entitled cause, and being fully advised in the premises;

It is Hereby Ordered that the Clerk of the Court pay to the said J. Richard Lane, the sum of Ninety-three and 40/100 Dollars ($93.40), and deduct from the balance the sum of One Dollar as one per cent commission on the original deposit of One Hundred Dollars, and that the final balance of Five and 60/100 Dollars ($5.60) be returned to transferred to Jees & Costs a/c to the Credit of John J. Sullivan, Attorney for Petitioner.
div1.ab: Jeremiah Neterer United States District Judge
